## Accessing Results

```python
values = pro.component("zone_1").variable("temperature").values

df = pro.component("zone_1").variable_dataframe(
    units=True, frequency="M", value="mean", interval=None)
# frequency: None=sim step, "H", "D", "M", "Y"
# value: "mean", "max", "min", "sum"

sim.plot(pro.dates(), [pro.component("zone_1").variable("temperature")],
         names=["Zone"], frequency="D", value="mean")

pro.component("zone_1").parameter_dataframe()
pro.component_dataframe("Space")
```

## Tips

- Math expressions use plain Python syntax; variables come from `input_variables`
- Connect Year_schedule to HVAC setpoints and Space_type via `input_variables`
- Call `pro.check()` before `pro.simulate()` to validate all references
- `"INTERPOLATION"` shadow mode is faster; `"INSTANT"` is more accurate
